  "description": [
    "VOL XXXIII No Green Oranges Editor Florida Agriculturist Let the agitation against green or ange shipping go on Once I got out of the orange business 1 was mad disgusted I foresaw another collapse I figured it from half a dozen different standpoints One of which was de moralized markets resulting from dis graceful fruit I foresaw that our 9 people would always rush in their green sour fruit for fear of losing it from cold this because about four times in forty years we had the fruit slightly damaged Let me cite year be fore last My trees were injured enough to lose the foliage and largely the smallest wood the wood on which the leaves were Thermometer was as low as 17 degrees and yet the fruit was fine never rotted or soured but only dried out after awhile That same year the crop was larger than this year Now this fear of loss is largely what is the matter Sometimes one needs moneybut the right kind of a man should Iojt need it so bad as to endanger his own and his countrys future by shipping stuff that is a dis grace to his product For let"
  ],
